"Full bodied beer with a nice lingering flavor.  With the exception of sour it really touches all of your taste buds.  Even with all of the big flavors it's still reasonably smooth with a good carbonation level.  Starts slightly sweet  moving to slightly salty/earthy then goes to a nice not quite gritty bitter finish.  Really drinkable, as drinkable as any IPA you'd have that would be sub 7% and this IPL is 10%!  Great beer all around, Jack's Abby does it again."
